ight actually be the VisitableURLClassLoader. Gradle seems to use a custom classloader. I’m wondering if test classes are loaded into the application classloader. If that's the case, it raises concerns around the LambdaFactory and empty CLASS_FILE_TRANSFORMERS. To navigate this, I should find out whether I can call LambdaFactory.make and how to inject it properly.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining LambdaFactory and Byte Buddy**\\n\\nI'm trying to understand how the call sites in LambdaFactory.register relate to the test classloader. It looks like I need to invoke a private method in the system's LambdaFactory, but direct access without reflection may not be feasible. I'm considering whether I can use the public API of AgentBuilder to handle lambda instrumentation instead. Maybe I could write a test that triggers the AgentBuilder's LambdaInstrumentationStrategy, but I need to explore how Byte Buddy works with lambda instrumentation and the role of LambdaFactory.register in that process.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_QEs28NjpKfbP2E3icvuBCJR6|fc_07103d4a18b3d323016a2922a976288193b1af2100e6bffa84", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.request, zipfile, io\nurl='https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/net/bytebuddy/byte-buddy-dep/1.14.4/byte-buddy-dep-1.14.4-sources.jar'\ndata=urllib.request.urlopen(url, timeout=15).read()\nz=zipfile.ZipFile(io.BytesIO(data))\nfor name in z.namelist():\n if name.endswith('.java'):\n  text=z.read(name).decode(errors='ignore')\n  if 'LambdaFactory.register' in text or 'LambdaFactory.release' in text or 'LambdaFactory.make' in text:\n   print('---',name)\n   idx=0\n   for needle in ['LambdaFactory.register','LambdaFactory.release','LambdaFactory.make']:\n    i=text.find(needle)\n    if i>=0: print(text[max(0,i-1000):i+1000])\nPY", "timeout": 30}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1634, "output": 1684, "cacheRead": 23552, "cache