t actually be the VisitableURLClassLoader. Gradle seems to use a custom classloader. I’m wondering if test classes are loaded into the application classloader. If that's the case, it raises concerns around the LambdaFactory and empty CLASS_FILE_TRANSFORMERS. To navigate this, I should find out whether I can call LambdaFactory.make and how to inject it properly.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining LambdaFactory and Byte Buddy**\\n\\nI'm trying to understand how the call sites in LambdaFactory.register relate to the test classloader. It looks like I need to invoke a private method in the system's LambdaFactory, but direct access without reflection may not be feasible. I'm considering whether I can use the public API of AgentBuilder to handle lambda instrumentation instead. Maybe I could write a test that triggers the AgentBuilder's LambdaInstrumentationStrategy, but I need to explore how Byte Buddy works with lambda instrumentation and the role of LambdaFactory.register in that process.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_QEs28NjpKfbP2E3icvuBCJR6|fc_07103d4a18b3d323016a2922a976288193b1af2100e6bffa84", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.request, zipfile, io\nurl='https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/net/bytebuddy/byte-buddy-dep/1.14.4/byte-buddy-dep-1.14.4-sources.jar'\ndata=urllib.request.urlopen(url, timeout=15).read()\nz=zipfile.ZipFile(io.BytesIO(data))\nfor name in z.namelist():\n if name.endswith('.java'):\n  text=z.read(name).decode(errors='ignore')\n  if 'LambdaFactory.register' in text or 'LambdaFactory.release' in text or 'LambdaFactory.make' in text:\n   print('---',name)\n   idx=0\n   for needle in ['LambdaFactory.register','LambdaFactory.release','LambdaFactory.make']:\n    i=text.find(needle)\n    if i>=0: print(text[max(0,i-1000):i+1000])\nPY", "timeout": 30}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1634, "output": 1684, "cacheRead": 23552, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 26870, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781080700547, "responseId": "resp_07103d4a18b3d323016a29227cfd68819390972039f0e4f8e9"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_QEs28NjpKfbP2E3icvuBCJR6|fc_07103d4a18b3d323016a2922a976288193b1af2100e6bffa84", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "--- net/bytebuddy/agent/builder/AgentBuilder.java\nses representing lambda expressions that are created by Byte Buddy are fully compatible to those created by\n         * the JVM and can be serialized or deserialized to one another. The classes do however show a few differences:\n         * <ul>\n         * <li>Byte Buddy's classes are public with a public executing transformer. Doing so, it is not necessary to instantiate a\n         * non-capturing lambda expression by reflection. This is done because Byte Buddy is not necessarily capable\n         * of using reflection due to an active security manager.</li>\n         * <li>Byte Buddy's classes are not marked as synthetic as an agent builder does not instrument synthetic classes\n         * by default.</li>\n         * </ul>\n         */\n        ENABLED {\n            @Override\n            protected void apply(ByteBuddy byteBuddy,\n                                 Instrumentation instrumentation,\n                                 ClassFileTransformer classFileTransformer) {\n                if (LambdaFactory.register(classFileTransformer, new LambdaInstanceFactory(byteBuddy))) {\n                    Class<?> lambdaMetaFactory;\n                    try {\n                        lambdaMetaFactory = Class.forName(\"java.lang.invoke.LambdaMetafactory\");\n                    } catch (ClassNotFoundException ignored) {\n                        return;\n                    }\n                    byteBuddy.with(Implementation.Context.Disabled.Factory.INSTANCE)\n                            .redefine(lambdaMetaFactory)\n                            .method(ElementMatchers.<MethodDescription>isPublic().and(named(\"metafactory\")))\n                            .intercept(new Implementation.Simple(LambdaMetafactoryFactory.REGULAR))\n                            .method(ElementMatchers.<MethodDescription>isPublic().and(named(\"altMetafactory\")))\n                            .intercept(new Implementation.Simple(LambdaMetafactoryFactory.ALTERNATIVE))\n                            .make()\n                       \nn,\n                                 ClassFileTransformer classFileTransformer) {\n                /* do nothing */\n            }\n\n            @Override\n            protected boolean isInstrumented(@MaybeNull Class<?> type) {\n                return type == null || !type.getName().contains(\"/\");\n            }\n        };\n\n        /**\n         * Releases the supplied class file transformer when it was built with {@link AgentBuilder#with(LambdaInstrumentationStrategy)} enabled.\n         * Subsequently, the class file transformer is no longer applied when a class that represents a lambda expression is created.\n         *\n         * @param classFileTransformer The class file transformer to release.\n         * @param instrumentation      The instrumentation instance that is used to potentially rollback the instrumentation of the {@code LambdaMetafactory}.\n         */\n        public static void release(ClassFileTransformer classFileTransformer, Instrumentation instrumentation) {\n            if (LambdaFactory.release(classFileTransformer)) {\n                try {\n                    ClassReloadingStrategy.of(instrumentation).reset(Class.forName(\"java.lang.invoke.LambdaMetafactory\"));\n                } catch (Exception exception) {\n                    throw new IllegalStateException(\"Could not release lambda transformer\", exception);\n                }\n            }\n        }\n\n        /**\n         * Returns an enabled lambda instrumentation strategy for {@code true}.\n         *\n         * @param enabled If lambda instrumentation should be enabled.\n         * @return {@code true} if the returned strategy should be enabled.\n         */\n        public static LambdaInstrumentationStrategy of(boolean enabled) {\n            return enabled\n                    ? ENABLED\n                    : DISABLED;\n        }\n\n        /**\n         * Applies a transformation to lambda instances if applicable.\n         *\n         * @param byteBuddy            The Byte Buddy instance to use.\n         * @\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1781080747033}]}
